    title='Conclusion'
    description='Encrption is a frontier'
    keywords='conclution,frontier,rsa,diffie-helman'
    path='conclusion'
    image='coder-default-bg.jpeg'
    imageCaption='Image of a Programer, Jefferson Santos, November 17th 2017'
>
    <Text type='section'>
        <Text type='p'>
            {`As previously said, asymmetrical encryption is a frontier on how people communicate, obtain information, and how the government protects itself. The groundbreaking ever-growing frontier of encryption allows people to send encrypted emails to one another without worry that others could eavesdrop on the communication. In addition to protecting personal information and equipment, governments rely on encryption to protect their own data so they can convey sensitive information for example, strategic plans and communications with agents of espionage. If it was unencrypted, others can simply steal this data which potentially can get a person killed. Finally, encryption boosts the credibility of information on websites, as people are assured that information on websites is what they intended the people to see, allowing people today to continue to use and trust the internet as a credible source of information. Because of the aforementioned reasons, (encryption protecting the general public, the government, and the accuracy of the things we search), encryption is one of the greatest frontiers of today.`}
        </Text>
    </Text>

